British Secretary of State for International Development, Priti Patel was hosted to a cocktail at High Commissioner Nic Hailey s residence in Muthaiga on Sunday evening.The event brought together Kenyan entrepreneurs who ve received UK funding to develop digital technology for various development initiatives.Present were Kenya Agribusiness and Agroindustry Alliance chief executive Lucy Muchoki , Adam Smith International regional director Gareth O Hagan, Sanergy co-founder David Auerbach, Movapay chief executive James Mwaniki and KPMG East Africa chief executive officer Josphat Mwaura.